body:
To define a federated database instance store for an Atlas Online Archive, you can
specify the following JSON (Javascript Object Notation) configuration parameters in your
[setStorageConfig](adf-setstorageconfig).
The configuration contains the Atlas online archive and maps it to virtual
collections that you can query.

The following JSON (Javascript Object Notation) configuration shows the format of the
[stores](adf-oa-stores-reference) and [databases](adf-oa-databases-reference)
configuration fields, which you must set in your Federated Database Instance configuration
file to define an Atlas Online Archive as a federated database instance store:

```json
{
  "stores" : [
    {
      "name" : "<string>",
      "provider": "<string>",
      "region": "<string>"
    }
  ],
  "databases" : [
      {
        "name" : "<string>",
        "collections" : [
          {
            "name" : "<string>",
            "dataSources" : [
              {
                "storeName" : "<string>",
                "datasetName" : "<string>",
                "datasetPrefix": "<string>",
                "trimLevel": <int>,
                "provenanceFieldName": "<string>",
                "maxDatasets": <int>
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "views" : [ 
          {
            "name" : "<string>", 
            "source" : "<string>", 
            "pipeline" : "<string>" 
          }
        ] 
      }
  ]
}

```

The JSON configuration for Atlas Online Archive data stores contains
two top-level objects: [stores](adf-oa-stores-reference) and
[databases](adf-oa-databases-reference).
